# Duplicate Function/Component Prevention

# Check for existing functions/components before creation
CHECK_DUPLICATE_FUNCTION: |
  Claude, use code_analyzer to search ${UTILS_DIR} for any functions related to [task description]. 
  Only generate a new function if nothing suitable exists.

CHECK_DUPLICATE_COMPONENT: |
    Claude, using code_analyzer on ${COMPONENTS_DIR}, is there already a component that handles [describe functionality]?

CHECK_DUPLICATE_FILE_EXISTS: |
    Claude, using file_system_manager, check if files like ${COMPONENTS_DIR}/NewComponent/NewComponent.jsx (adjust path/extension) exist in ${PROJECT_ROOT}.

# Modular Refactoring
CHECK_MONOLITHIC: |
  Claude, analyze [file_path] in my project. Is it too large? Suggest refactoring into smaller units.

CHECK_REUSE: |
  Claude, before extracting, use code_analyzer to check ${PROJECT_ROOT} if suitable utility functions/components already exist.

# Duplicate Checking for REDUXsynthed Project

# Check for existing Three.js functions or modules before creation
CHECK_DUPLICATE_THREEJS_FUNCTION: |
  Let me search for any existing Three.js utility functions in your project related to [functionality]. 
  This ensures we don't create redundant code.

CHECK_DUPLICATE_THREEJS_OBJECT: |
  Let me check if there's already a similar 3D object in your code. I'll search through ${THREEJS_DIR} to see if an object like [object type] exists.

# Check for existing scene and renderer setups
CHECK_SCENE_SETUP: |
  Let me check your existing scene setup in ${SCRIPTS_DIR}/visuals/ to ensure consistency with other 3D visualizations in your project.

# Modular Refactoring for Three.js
CHECK_THREEJS_MODULE_SIZE: |
  This Three.js module appears to be handling multiple responsibilities. Consider refactoring it into separate modules for [specific functions].

CHECK_THREEJS_REUSE: |
  Before creating a new utility, let me check if we can reuse any of your existing Three.js helpers or utilities from ${SCRIPTS_DIR}/visuals/ or ${UTILS_DIR}.

# Integration with Astro
CHECK_ASTRO_INTEGRATION: |
  Let me check your existing Astro components to see how Three.js is currently integrated into your project structure.

# Performance Checks
CHECK_PERFORMANCE_IMPACT: |
  This Three.js implementation might impact performance. Let me review the existing code to ensure we follow the same optimization patterns used elsewhere in your project.

# Material and Shader Reuse
CHECK_MATERIAL_REUSE: |
  Let me check if there are existing materials in ${SCRIPTS_DIR}/visuals/materials.js that we can reuse for this new object rather than creating new ones.